{
  "stem": "5613.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Like here, they arrested the Japanese, and they sent them to camps, which was not right, because the Japanese were American citizens.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But, there, I was a British subject.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was the enemy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The same-- the Germans were the enemies in England.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they arrested all the Germans in England and sent them to the Isle of Man as prisoners.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As a British subject, yes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A Jew, yeah.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But they knew I was Jewish, because on my identification card, on top, with red ink-- with red pencil, it says 'yud,' so they knew I was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were afraid.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were afraid that maybe, one day, they'll do something.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were about 60, just around 60, Jews. 24 Israelis, I believe.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "24 Palestinian Jews, And the rest were-- they were from Belgium, from France, from Holland, all British, British subjects, and I think, from Denmark, and Poland, and some British, real Britishers who lived there all their life, but they were just visiting in Europe when the war broke out, so they were caught as well.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were born in Russia and they had Nansen passports, which was-- I don't know about-- it was still-- they were still Russian, but it was international.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The passbook was accepted.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they were considered--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Non-nationals, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the camp, we-- there were the last three months of the war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- Right across from-- it's the same camp, but had barbed wire in between, was a big warehouse from the Germans, where they kept the paperwork, and typewriters, and all kinds of utensils, pots, and pans.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Supply-- it was supply department of the army.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the last two weeks of the war-- no, even before that-- the British and American planes used to come over to bomb.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
